&lt;p&gt;It is located on the border of Wales and provides the gateway to the Brecon Beacons to the west and Malvern Hills and Worcestershire to the east.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trainee Dental Nurse, Full time 37.5 hours/week,&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;work plan will include one out of hours session per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome all applicants who meet the essential criteria for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a Trainee Dental Nurse to provide excellent support to the dental team within the Dental Access Centre. Dental Nurses provide chair-side support to Dentists and Therapists and play a key role in the patient support and also have responsibility for infection control and health and safety in the workplace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be a dental nurse you will need to have excellent communication skills, caring nature and be highly organised,dedicated to providing the smooth and efficient running of the surgery in providing a high standard of dental care to the patients exclusively NHS routine and urgent dental care to people of all ages including those varied special care/additional needs and those who have had difficulty accessing GDS NHS dental care at sites across Herefordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be provided on the job as well as attending an accredited course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to travel across Herefordshire in the delivery of dental care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
